These curves displayed in Fig. 3b revealed that, compared to the conventional silicon solar cell presented as a dotted line, the light absorbed in the SiGe layer decreases slowly the contribution of light-generated current in the space-charge region (curves 2) and the base region (curves 3). This result is attributed to the fact that the carriers-generated rate in the crystalline silicon decreases with the αSiGe\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
